  (1) BC-INFO1 (bootstrap-check.sh) — env-var trust boundary, PASS. Both git-discovery calls are now sanitized identically: stdin.cwd walk-up (L163-164) and cold path (L185-186) both run under `env -u GIT_DIR -u GIT_WORK_TREE -u GIT_COMMON_DIR -u GIT_INDEX_FILE`. grep confirms these are the ONLY two `git rev-parse --show-toplevel` invocations in the file and both are wrapped — no residual unsanitized discovery in the resolution function. GIT_CEILING_DIRECTORIES preservation is safe: ceiling can only *narrow* (bound) discovery upward, never redirect to a decoy repo, so leaving it intact does not reopen the latch-a-decoy vector. Fail-closed verified: cold path falls through git -> $PWD -> `return 11` (resolution failure) so a poisoned env cannot silently latch a wrong project_dir.

  (2) job-stop (rein.sh) — command injection / atomic writes / TOCTOU, PASS. No injection: `jid` is the operator-supplied CLI arg used only in deterministic path construction ($jd/$jid.status|.exit|.json|.pid); `pid` is read from rein's own .pid file and used only in `kill`/`kill -0`/arithmetic; no eval, no word-split-vulnerable expansion of job metadata. The python3 meta patch uses a single-quoted heredoc (<<'PY') so no bash expansion of the script body, receives args via sys.argv (int(sys.argv[2]) for rc), parses meta with json.load (data-only, NOT unsafe deserialization — JSON cannot execute code), and writes via temp+os.replace (atomic). State files written via write_atomic (temp + mv -f). Signal handling targets only the resolved pid/pgid. The documented sub-ms TOCTOU has NO security impact: it cannot redirect a write to an unintended path, execute code, or escalate privilege — worst case is a benign status overwrite, now further narrowed by the compare-and-set guard.

  (3) job-stop compare-and-set guard (unstaged delta, rein.sh) — hardening, PASS. Adds a read-before-write check (cur_status == "running" AND .pid present) that early-returns to avoid clobbering a natural wrapper settlement. This tightens behavior; no security regression. Regression tests (e)/(e2) added.

  (4) G8-3 (rein-codex-review.sh x2, byte-identical) — injection / path traversal / gate integrity, PASS. SPEC_REVIEW_SUBJECT is sed-extracted from the marker's first line and flows ONLY into CHANGED_FILES, which is interpolated into a quoted heredoc (<<CTX) sent to codex as text — no file-read, no git command, no eval on the value, so no path traversal or injection surface. In spec-review mode SAD_PATH is set empty and ALL downstream parsing (_parse_dod_plan_ref, head -1 "$SAD_PATH", _parse_dod_covers, plan_ref/design_ref/covers) is guarded by `[ -n "$SAD_PATH" ]`, so no file read occurs on the empty/sentinel path. Gate integrity NOT weakened: write_code_review_stamp (.codex-reviewed) remains reachable ONLY when REIN_REVIEW_MODE = "code-review" AND verdict = PASS (L949-952); spec-review mode still writes no stamp and never touches .review-pending (L954-959). The G8-3 changes do not touch the mode-decision regex or the stamping branch — no bypass introduced.

